metadata.prompt:
[Intro]:
[Soft piano and strings setting a reflective tone]

[Verse 1]:
Whispers in the twilight, shadows in the dawn
A heart once filled with silence, now seeks to carry on
In the depths of sorrow, where dreams begin to fade
The light within my spirit, guides me through the shade

[Chorus]:
Though my heart may fracture, and dreams may come undone
I’ll rise from shadows, I’ll rise to greet the sun
With every tear that’s fallen, a new day will arise
I’ll rise from shadows, beneath these endless skies

[Verse 2]:
Beneath the weight of echoes, the past begins to speak
Through the fragments of my longing, the future I shall seek
Amidst the broken pieces, a melody takes flight
From the ashes of my sorrow, I’ll emerge into the light

[Chorus]:
Though my heart may fracture, and dreams may come undone
I’ll rise from shadows, I’ll rise to greet the sun
With every tear that’s fallen, a new day will arise
I’ll rise from shadows, beneath these endless skies

[Bridge]:
In the stillness of the midnight, reflections of the soul
Through the pain and through the darkness, I’ve learned to let it go
Every moment of despair, every whispered cry of pain
Has built the strength within me, I’ll rise and start again

[Verse 3]:
In the silent dawn of healing, the journey has begun
With every step I’m taking, I’ll find the strength to run
The path ahead is golden, lined with lessons learned
In the quiet of the morning, a new hope is discerned

[Chorus]:
Though my heart may fracture, and dreams may come undone
I’ll rise from shadows, I’ll rise to greet the sun
With every tear that’s fallen, a new day will arise
I’ll rise from shadows, beneath these endless skies

[Outro]:
[Soft piano and strings, fading out with a feeling of hope and renewal]

[Fade to End]:
[Echoing vocals and gentle instrumentation gradually fading]

[End]

(silence)
[End]

metadata.prompt:
[Instrumental intro]

[Verse 1]
With a paper umbrella, alone I tread,
Through a lingering lane where rain is shed.
Long it winds, desolate and stark,
A trail of silence in the watery dark.

[build-up]
[shakuhachi solo]

[Chorus]
I yearn to meet on this somber stroll,
A maiden with the sorrow of a soulful toll.
She'd harbour hues of lilac bloom,
A scent of sorrow...a perfumed gloom...

[drop]
[shakuhachi solo]

[Verse 2]
With melancholy tinted on her face,
The mourning hue of a lilac's grace.
In the rain, she grieves with quiet plea,
Lamenting, wandering, 
just like me.


[Chorus]
I yearn to meet on this somber stroll,
A maiden with the sorrow of a soulful toll.
She'd harbour hues of lilac bloom,
A scent of sorrow...a perfumed gloom...

[shakuhachi solo]

[drop]

[Verse 3]
As she silently comes nearer, with a sighing gaze,
Her presence fleeting, like a lilac's dreamy haze.
Beside me drifts this lady, through the dreamscape wide,
Silent in her movement, 
yet overwhelmingly implied...



yet overwhelmingly implied...

[Chorus]
I yearn to meet on this somber stroll,
A maiden with the sorrow of a soulful toll.
She'd harbour hues of lilac bloom,
A scent of sorrow...a perfumed gloom...

[shakuhachi solo]

[drop]

[Bridge]
She then moves away, farther, to the crumbling fence,
Walking through this rainy lane, her absence intense.
In the rain's lament, her color fades into the night,
Her fragrance, her sigh-like look, her melancholy light...

[Outro]
With my paper umbrella, alone I wander in this extended lane,
Long, long and deserted, where the rain sings of pain.
I hoped for one like lilac, bound in mournful grace,
A maiden wrapped in sorrow, 
vanishing without a trace...
[shakuhachi solo]
[fade to end]
[end]

[Outro]
With my paper umbrella, alone I wander in this extended lane,
Long, long and deserted, where the rain sings of pain.
I hoped for one like lilac, bound in mournful grace,
A maiden wrapped in sorrow, 
vanishing without a trace...
[shakuhachi solo]
[fade to end]
[end]

metadata.prompt:
400g of pasta (spaghetti, penne, or any pasta of your choice)
2 tablespoons of olive oil
1 small onion, finely chopped
2 garlic cloves, minced
800g of canned crushed tomatoes
Salt and pepper, to taste
A handful of fresh basil leaves, chopped (optional)
Grated Parmesan cheese, for serving (optional)

Start by boiling your pasta in a large pot of salted water according to the package's instructions until it reaches al dente perfection. While that's cooking away, grab a skillet and heat up some olive oil over a medium flame. Toss in your finely chopped onion and give it a stir until it becomes soft, which should take about 5 minutes. Follow that up with the minced garlic, letting it cook for another minute to unleash its aroma. Next up, pour in your crushed tomatoes, seasoning the mixture with a bit of salt and pepper to taste. Allow the sauce to simmer gently for around 20 minutes, giving those flavors time to really come together. If you notice your sauce getting a bit too thick, don't hesitate to thin it out with a splash of the pasta water you smartly reserved earlier.
